<taxonomicName id="4C7B4D12FFD7B327FDE04FFAFD1DF912" authorityName="C.A.Viraktamath" authorityYear="2011" box="[588,716,1729,1753]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Formallia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ishiharai">
<emphasis id="B90FEA83FFD7B327FDE04FFAFD1DF912" box="[588,716,1729,1753]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">F. ishiharai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C7B4D12FFD7B327FCA84FFAFC45F912" authorityName="C.A.Viraktamath" authorityYear="2011" box="[772,916,1729,1753]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Formallia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longipenis">
<emphasis id="B90FEA83FFD7B327FCA84FFAFC45F912" box="[772,916,1729,1753]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">F. longipenis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but differs in having an elongate inner arm of the male style and lacking hair-like setae on the subgenital plates.
</paragraph>
